# Snapshot: code/if_blocks

## Case 01

### Source: `test/tmp_fs/code.frog`

```frog
1 2 == if do 5 else 7 end print
```

### Run and Build

Commands:

```text
py -m frog run test/tmp_fs/code.frog
py -m frog -l WARN build -r test/tmp_fs/code.frog
```

Output:

```text
[ERROR] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:11: condition part of InstructionType.IF should put exactly one BOOL on the stack
[NOTE] expected_stack:
      0. BOOL()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:5
[NOTE] actual_stack: (empty)
[EXIT CODE] 1
```

